SIMPLE: unjust
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unjust
<hw>Un*just"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Acting
contrary to the standard of right; not animated or controlled by
justice; false; dishonest; <as>as, an <ex>unjust</ex> man or
judge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contrary to justice and right; prompted by a spirit
of injustice; wrongful; <as>as, an <ex>unjust</ex> sentence; an
<ex>unjust</ex> demand; an <ex>unjust</ex> accusation.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*just"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*just"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unjustice</ent>⟦br⟧
